# ── Elixir / Erlang / Phoenix ──
# deps/, _build/ and .elixir_ls/ are already ignored above; these add the rest of
# the standard `mix phx.new` artifact set, non-anchored so a Phoenix app added in
# a subdir (e.g. phoenix/) is covered too. The app-relative paths (priv/static/
# assets, doc/, the hex tarball, config secrets) belong in the app's own
# .gitignore, which `mix phx.new` generates when a Phoenix app is scaffolded.
erl_crash.dump
*.beam
*.ez
cover/
.elixir-tools/
.lexical/
# SQLite stores — the cms content store (`cms build --load`) and any Phoenix Ecto
# dev/test databases — are already covered by the *.db / *.db-shm / *.db-wal rules
# at the top of this file.

# aaw MCP server workspace state (scope index; reconstructable). The glob
# pair (not the directory form) keeps the committable policy file visible —
# a bare negation under a directory-form ignore is a git no-op (W-3, D-9).
.aaw/*
!.aaw/config.json
